                        <h3 class="mb-4">Documentation</h3>

                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-12 form-group">
                                <b>This API is simple to use. You just have to follow these steps</b><br><br>

                                <ul>
                                    <li><a href="/{{ lang }}/create-account">Create a free account</a></li>
                                    <li>Click on the link you receive by email to confirm your address</li>
                                    <li>Generate a token with credentials</li>

                                    <p>You can use any language to make this CURL call. (Python, PHP, Java, JavaScript...)</p>

                                    <textarea class="codeBlock" rows="8">curl --location --request POST 'http://anti-virus-api.com/api/login_check' \
                                        --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
                                        --data-raw '{"username":"YOUR_LOGIN","password":"YOUR_PASSWORD"}'
                                    </textarea> <br>

                                    If your credentials are correct, our server will provide you with a token as a response :
                                    <textarea class="codeBlock" rows="8">{"token": "YOUR_TOKEN","refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN"}
                                    </textarea>
                                    <br>
                                    YOUR_TOKEN is valid for one hour, its duration can be extended using YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN
                                    <br><br>

                                    <br><br>
                                    <li>Use the token to upload the file on our server </li>

                                    <textarea class="codeBlock" rows="16">curl --location --request POST 'http://anti-virus-api.local.com/api/files/upload' \
                                        --header 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \
                                        --form 'file=@"file.pdf"' \
                                        --form 'description="My awesome file"'
                                    </textarea>

                                    <br><br>
                                    <li>A refresh token is a credential artifact that lets a client application get new access tokens without having to ask the user to log in again </li>

                                    <textarea class="codeBlock" rows="16">curl --location --request POST 'http://anti-virus-api.local.com/api/files/upload' \
                                        --header 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \
